**Title:** CON - CTF Blue Team Style

**Organizer:** VinceK

**Description:** Welcome to the Capture the Flag game designed to hone your skills on the blue team side of cybersecurity. This challenge is crafted to test your proficiency in areas such as digital forensics, network forensics, malware analysis, hashing/encryption, threat intelligence, OSINT, scripting, and more. The mission is to unravel the who, what, when, where, and why of a cyber-attack by analyzing provided digital forensics data, log files, and cyber threat intelligence data.

**Game Format:**
- **Team or Solo Play:** Participate alone or with a team of 3-4 members.
- **Online Portal:** Access the game through an online portal for setting up teams, viewing challenges, and submitting findings.
- **Tools and Setup:** Compatible with any operating system; files or tools may need to be downloaded for analysis.
- **Scoring:** Real-time scoreboard to track team progress.

**Rules of Engagement:**
- Respect the platform, do not attack the game scoreboard or other players’ challenges.
- Fair play is encouraged; intentionally disrupting other players' challenges is prohibited.
- Scoring is dynamic; frequently solved challenges will decrease in point value.

**Who Can Participate:** The game welcomes participants of all skill levels, from curious beginners to seasoned cybersecurity professionals.

**Additional Information:**
- **Event URL:** [CTF Blue Team Style](https://saintcon.org/con-ctf-blue-team-style/)
- **Event Image:** ![CTF Blue Team Style Splash](http://www.saintcon.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/CTFBlueTeamStyleSplash2024.png)

